    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but if the movement was so successful at forcing change, does that mean the nonviolent stuff was the only way that actually worked? i've heard people argue that the more radical or militant groups were a bigger reason why the government finally moved. was the nonviolent approach basically the only legitimate path there, or were those other groups actually more effective at creating real change?",
